\section{Problems in Agriculture in India and possible solutions(Government Roles):-}

\subsection{Problems}

\textbf{i)} The agricultural system in India is too much rainfall specifically monsoon dependent. The dry parts of India is not as good in agricultural activities.

\vspace{2 mm}
\hspace{-5 mm}\textbf{ii)}The temperature also plays a crucial role in agriculture. The day by day temperature increasing i.e Global warming affect the agriculture.

\vspace{2 mm}
\hspace{-5 mm}\textbf{iii)} In some of the crops we see that it's production is decreasing day by day. This means the farmers of that particular crop may loose interest for production due to low price of crop or high value of pesticides, fertilizers etc or in that region not such kind of high level technology are used.

\subsection{Possible solution}

Government have already taken several schemes like:- 

\textbf{1)\textcolor{blue}{e-NAM (National Agriculture Market)}}: For digital and unified market integration.

\vspace{2 mm}
\hspace{-5 mm}\textbf{2)\textcolor{blue}{Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima Yojana (PMFBY)}:} For crop insurance and risk mitigation.

\vspace{2 mm}
\hspace{-5 mm}\textbf{3)\textcolor{blue}{Soil Health Cards}:}  To promote judicious use of fertilizers.

\vspace{2 mm}
\hspace{-5 mm}\textbf{4)\textcolor{blue}{Agri-Infra Fund}:} For post-harvest management and infrastructure.

\vspace{2 mm}
\hspace{-5 mm}\textbf{5)\textcolor{blue}{Farm Laws (now repealed): }:}Though controversial, they aimed to liberalize agri-markets.

\vspace{2 mm}
beside this government should also:

\vspace{2 mm}
i) inspire the farmers to harvest new crops.

ii) Make institute to teach them about the use of new technologies.

iii) Try to fix the market price for each crop so that they can get great energy and enthusiasm in their work.
